questions.explanation:
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Agnostic&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;An &lt;strong&gt;agnostic &lt;/strong&gt;is someone who is not sure about the existence of God.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The other options are not suitable because:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adjure &lt;/strong&gt;means to beg or plead with someone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anarchist &lt;/strong&gt;is someone who believes in the abolition of government and law.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cardigan &lt;/strong&gt;is a type of sweater.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;agnostic &lt;/strong&gt;is derived from the Greek word &amp;#39;a&amp;#39; (meaning &amp;#39;not&amp;#39;) and &amp;#39;gnosis&amp;#39; (meaning &amp;#39;knowledge&amp;#39;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agnosticism &lt;/strong&gt;is the view that the existence or non-existence of God is unknown and perhaps unknowable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agnostics &lt;/strong&gt;typically argue that there is not enough evidence to prove or disprove the existence of God.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Corroborate&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning&amp;nbsp;of the marked option:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Corroborate-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;confirm or give support to (a statement, theory, or finding)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meanings of the other given options:&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Philanthropist-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;a person who seeks to promote the welfare of others, especially by the generous donation of money to good causes&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Bilingual-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;(of a person) speaking two languages fluently&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Refute-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;prove (a statement or theory) to be wrong or false; disprove&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, from the given meanings, we find that&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Corroborate &lt;/strong&gt;is the correct&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;one-word substitute.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 3&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;dactylology&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means the use of fingers and hands to communicate and convey ideas, commonly referred to as sign language. (हस्ताक्षर भाषा)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;She learned dactylology to communicate with her deaf friend.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Braille&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;refers to a system of raised dots that can be read with the fingers by people who are blind or who have low vision. (ब्रेल)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;He reads books in Braille.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, we can infer that the correct one-word substitute for the given statement is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;dactylology&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Braille &lt;/strong&gt;(ब्रेल): A system of reading and writing for the blind, using raised dots.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; He reads books in Braille.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Morse Code &lt;/strong&gt;(मॉर्स कोड): A system of sending messages that uses long and short sounds, lights, or marks to represent letters and numbers.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;They communicated using Morse code during the war.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dermatology&lt;/strong&gt; (त्वचाविज्ञान): The branch of medicine dealing with the skin and its diseases.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; She visited a dermatologist for her skin condition.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 2 i.e. dirge.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meanings of the given words-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flux &lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;the action or process of flowing or flowing out.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dirge&lt;/strong&gt; means&amp;nbsp;a mournful song, piece of music, or sound.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Elixir&lt;/strong&gt; means&amp;nbsp;a magical or medicinal potion.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hymn&lt;/strong&gt; means&amp;nbsp;a religious song or poem of praise to God or a god.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;dirge&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is the most appropriate answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;38px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/quesImage45.png&quot; width=&quot;160px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;You may think that option 4 is the answer as both options 2 and 4 are songs. But after looking at the meanings, we can infer that &lt;strong&gt;option 2&lt;/strong&gt; is correct.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Gambit.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Gambit&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means a calculated move, especially in chess, made to gain an advantage. (विशेष रूप से शतरंज में, लाभ प्राप्त करने के लिए की गई एक सोची-समझी चाल)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;He played his &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;gambit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; by sacrificing his knight to gain control of the center of the board.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is a noun and is pronounced as gam-bit.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is Option 2.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grunt&lt;/strong&gt;: a low, guttural sound made by an animal or person, often expressing dissatisfaction or pain. (अरुचि व्&amp;zwj;यंजक बुड़बुड़ाहट)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Profit&lt;/strong&gt;: a financial gain or benefit, especially the difference between the amount earned and the amount spent in buying, operating, or producing something. (लागत से अधिक दाम पर बेचने से प्राप्&amp;zwj;त धन; नफ़ा, लाभ, फ़ायदा)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonsai&lt;/strong&gt;: a Japanese art form using miniature trees grown in containers that mimic the shape and scale of full-size trees. (गमले में उगाया जानेवाला एक छोटा वृक्ष जिसकी सामान्य वृद्धि को अवरुद्ध कर दिया गया हो; वामन वृक्ष; बोंसाई)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is-&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Cardiologist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the marked option:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Cardiologist:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;a doctor who specializes in treating diseases of the heart&amp;nbsp;(एक डॉक्टर जो दिल की बीमारियों के इलाज में माहिर है)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;In six programmes, eligibility to the exercise component of the programme was decided by a &lt;strong&gt;cardiologist&lt;/strong&gt; or a physiotherapist.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;L et&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the other given options:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Pediatrician&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;a doctor who has special training in medical care for children&amp;nbsp;(एक डॉक्टर जिसके पास बच्चों की चिकित्सा देखभाल में विशेष प्रशिक्षण है)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Neurologist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​​:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;a doctor who studies and treats diseases of the nerves&amp;nbsp;(एक डॉक्टर जो नसों के रोगों का अध्ययन और उपचार करता है)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Pathologist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;an expert in the study of diseases, especially someone who examines a dead person&amp;#39;s body and cuts it open to discover how they died&amp;nbsp;(रोगों के अध्ययन में एक विशेषज्ञ, विशेष रूप से कोई व्यक्ति जो किसी मृत व्यक्ति के शरीर की जांच करता है और उसे यह पता लगाने के लिए खोलता है कि उनकी मृत्यु कैसे हुई)&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, from the given meanings, we find that&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Cardiologist&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the correct one-word substitute.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Match the following definitions with their one-word substitutes.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;A&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Careful examination of your own thoughts and feelings&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;big&gt;&amp;nbsp; i&amp;nbsp; &lt;/big&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Fratricide&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;B&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A short amusing or interesting story about a real incident or person&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; ii&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Dipsomania&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;C&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;The act of killing of one&amp;#39;s brother&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; iii&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Anecdote&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; D&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;An intense, excess craving for alcoholic beverages to excess&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;iv&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Introspection&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A-iv, B-iii, C-i, D-ii&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let us see the meanings of the words:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Fratricide&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; &amp;rArr; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The action of killing one&amp;#39;s brother.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Dipsomania&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; &amp;rArr; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Alcoholism, specifically in a form characterized by intermittent bouts of craving for alcohol.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Anecdote&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; &amp;rArr; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A short interesting anecdote about a real incident or person&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Introspection&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; &amp;rArr; &lt;span&gt;The examination or observation of one&amp;#39;s own mental and emotional processes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the above reference, we can see that the correct combination of matching is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A-iv, B-iii, C-i, D-ii&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;, which is given in &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Option 3&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

