&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;One-word substitutions are the combinations of different individual words to form a single meaning.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Release someone from a duty or obligation&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt; is called &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;exonerating.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amicable &lt;/strong&gt;meaning made or done in a friendly way, without argument.&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example- &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The leader was hoping to come to an amicable arrangement with everybody.&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct one-word substitution for&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Someone&amp;nbsp;friendly and good-natured is Amicable&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
